g.title: EleanorRank4Convo6 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank4Convo6 begins.

g.title: j2776708023
g.text: So… why crystals?

g.title: j1026614272
g.text: So. You and Quincy. Have you ever... y'know?

g.title: j4127126992
g.text: Oh, I’ve always loved them. When I was little, my dad took us to the Innovation Museum in Ludston and Arthur and I both got these crystal growing kits. Arthur’s turned out shit, literally like a lumpy little rock turd. It went in the bin. Mine was a beautiful blue diamond. Ever since that day I’ve felt like crystals were on my side, somehow.

g.title: j764685712
g.text: Okay, I'm feeling generous today, so I'll give you this one for free.

g.title: j1637194991
g.text: So they’re just for decoration, then?

g.title: j2216842230
g.text: We have never. We have not even slightly.

g.title: j309763631
g.text: Ah. No.

g.title: j3620345949
g.text: I cannot help thinking that Quincy's preferred position would be 'partner on top holding a mirror, so he can imagine he's having sex with himself'.

g.title: j3548225519
g.text: I know there’s a lot of nonsense written about crystals. Not my thing. I don’t believe they purify my aura or light up my chakras.

g.title: j2259144016
g.text: No thank you. I'm content to admire from afar.

g.title: j2218934314
g.text: But they do have a presence.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j637231453
g.text: Sorry. I’m aware I sound like a complete headcase.

g.title: j1695732654
g.text: I'm glad you said it and not me. They're just fancy rocks.

g.title: j3070860345
g.text: I have friends who are Cephalons. They’re literally intelligences in the form of glass cubes. Why would you think I’d mock you for thinking crystals have a presence?

g.title: j1447431223
g.text: I spend too much time digging crystals out of the ground for them not to be important on some deeper level. You'd be amazed at how many Warframes were made in part by crystals of one kind or several.

g.title: j2282412336
g.text: Oh you are MADDENING sometimes.

g.title: j2174737769
g.text: Well, now I feel stupid for feeling stupid.

g.title: j3988647982
g.text: Amazed and intrigued!

g.title: j2965035469
g.text: I would have thought that you, of all people, could lift your perspective above the purely material.

g.title: j160013324
g.text: I expect you have crystals I could only dream about.

g.title: j856627520
g.text: Tell me, wise traveller, of the crystals of your time.

g.title: j2280759701
g.text: Away with you. Leave me to my fancy rocks.

g.title: j1895245480
g.text: Argon. You only find it in the Void, and it disintegrates once you take it out.

g.title: j2749417301
g.text: There’s a whole Warframe made of crystal. Citrine.

g.title: j3836695560
g.text: We have a pair of doomed lovers who were turned into crystal.

g.title: j1006072663
g.text: You say ‘you only find it in the Void’ like people are popping in and out of the Void all the time. I thought it was this crazy-making dimension, not a seaside resort.

g.title: j3195226608
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3011546836
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3943150400
g.text: I guess I didn’t tell you about Orokin Towers yet. They’re like strongholds in the Void, set up in case the Sentients tried to attack.

g.title: j683206782
g.text: That's her name? I think I glimpsed her in your mind!

g.title: j3179379874
g.text: How beautiful and sad. What must it be like, to become a monument to your love?

g.title: j3185195626
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j228170325
g.text: The pretty geode lady. I suppose she and I are related now. There's a comforting thought.

g.title: j3828626319
g.text: I hope nobody chips little bits off them as a keepsake. That would definitely happen in my time.

g.title: j8102993
g.text: Now that’s familiar. There are these top-security bunkers under Ludston and Mancunia. The idea is, if there’s ever a Radiation War, the fat cats and bigwigs get to hide down in their luxury bolthole and sip Mimosas while the rest of us get burned to a cinder up above.

g.title: j397288001
g.text: Welcome to the family, I guess?

g.title: j1837628686
g.text: People do try, but we keep them safe. It's the least we can do.

g.title: j373707662
g.text: Same old story, she said with a sigh.

g.title: j3095740295
g.text: It’s funny. Everyone was so scared of a Radiation War when I was growing up. I remember the public service broadcasts that used to go out. Sombre advice about how to stockpile supplies, how to prepare a refuge room, and how you really have to bury any dead relatives even if you don’t want to.

g.title: j3268813503
g.text: When I saw the reactor exploding in your mind, it took me right back to all those nightmares. I knew we had to stop it, whatever it took. I’d make the others believe you.

g.title: j3128430221
g.text: It’s not a Radiation War that’s waiting for this planet, though, is it? It’s the Techrot. One way or another, this loop’s going to work itself out and when it does, the rest of the world’s going to get infected.
